@startuml Question_Generation_Sequence
!theme plain
title RAG-based Question Generation Sequence

actor User
participant Frontend
participant "FastAPI Backend" as API
participant "RAG Service" as RAG
participant "Vector Service" as Vector
participant "Claude Service" as Claude
participant ChromaDB
participant "Claude API" as ClaudeAPI

User -> Frontend: Request question generation
Frontend -> API: POST /api/v1/generate-questions\n{topic, document_ids, count}

API -> RAG: generate_questions_from_documents()
RAG -> Vector: search_similar_content(topic, document_ids)

Vector -> ChromaDB: Query similar vectors
ChromaDB --> Vector: Relevant document chunks

Vector --> RAG: Context chunks with metadata
RAG -> RAG: Build RAG prompt with context

RAG -> Claude: generate_questions_with_context(prompt)
Claude -> ClaudeAPI: API request with context
ClaudeAPI --> Claude: Generated questions JSON

Claude -> Claude: Parse and validate response
Claude --> RAG: Structured questions

RAG -> RAG: Add source attribution
RAG --> API: Generated questions with sources

API --> Frontend: Questions with metadata
Frontend --> User: Display generated questions

note right of Vector
  Similarity search finds
  most relevant content
  for the given topic
end note

note right of Claude
  Rate limiting and
  retry logic ensure
  reliable generation
end note

note left of ClaudeAPI
  Costs are tracked
  and optimized per
  request
end note

@enduml
